headline: BKNG Q1 Earnings Call: Diversification and Direct Booking Strength Drive Outperformance
summary: Online travel agency Booking Holdings (NASDAQ:BKNG) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 7.9% year on year to $4.76 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $24.81 per share was 41.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Booking CFO leans on AI in push to run ‘tight ship’
summary: The online travel company is looking to slash costs by as much as $450 million by the end of 2027. It aims to reinvest some of the freed-up capital into AI projects.

headline: KAYAK reveals biggest savings and top trending locations for summer travellers
summary: Bucket-list destinations are closer than ever for jetsetters this summer, as new research from KAYAK, the world's leading travel search engine, reveals that flights to nearly half of the 150 most-searched summer holiday destinations from the UK have dropped in price compared to last year.
